parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of internal markings or streaks on the windshield can compromise its integrity, potentially leading to injuries or accidents if the windshield shatters or explodes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected explosion of the sunroof can cause injuries to occupants, especially those in the back seat, and may lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
The failure of the electronic throttle control system can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents.
The failure of the oil drain plug can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents, and potentially causing engine damage.
The failure of the transmission control system can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and stalling of the engine can cause a severe safety hazard, especially when driving at high speeds, as it can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: even when hitting the gas pedal; the engine lights illuminate on the dashboard; the engine makes a strange noise; the vehicle automatically shuts down while driving; the vehicle has difficulty starting or will not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical/wiring issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to safety hazards, such as engine stalling, loss of power, and difficulty starting the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine lights illuminate on the dashboard; the vehicle automatically shuts down while driving; the engine makes a strange noise; the vehicle has difficulty starting or will not start at all; a burning smell is present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate fuel economy estimates can lead to disappointment and financial losses for vehicle owners, as they may not achieve the expected mileage.
symptoms: The vehicle's actual fuel economy is lower than the estimated MPG provided by the dealer and manufacturer; the vehicle's fuel economy is inconsistent with the owner's driving habits.
